event: message_saved
data: {"messageId":"8J1ZPHc_leIF6k2BY_YuU","role":"user","content":"Perform a comprehensive cross-cloud cost analysis for our OpenAgentic infrastructure. Execute ALL of these steps:\n\n1. AWS Costs:\n   - Use aws_cost_summary to get the current month's total AWS spend\n   - Use aws_cost_by_service to break down costs by AWS service\n   - Use aws_identity to confirm which AWS account we're analyzing\n\n2. Azure Costs:\n   - Use azure_cost_query with timeframe 'MonthToDate' to get current Azure spend\n   - Use azure_cost_by_service with timeframe 'MonthToDate' for service breakdown\n   - Use azure_cost_forecast to project end-of-month costs\n   - Use azure_list_subscriptions to show which subscriptions are being billed\n\n3. Combined Analysis:\n   - Present a unified cost table showing both clouds side by side\n   - Identify the top 5 cost drivers across both clouds\n   - Calculate the projected monthly total\n   - Recommend at least 3 specific cost optimization opportunities\n   - Flag any services that seem anomalously expensive\n\nEven if some calls fail due to permissions, execute ALL of them and report what worked vs what didn't.","timestamp":"2026-02-20T22:00:38.044Z","source":"database","confirmed":true}

