data: {"index":0,"blockType":"text","finalContent":"---\n\n## Cross-Cloud Cost Analysis — Execution Report\n\n### Executive Summary\n\n**All 12 tool calls failed** with the identical error: `ECONNREFUSED 10.43.224.106:8080`. The MCP proxy backend that brokers access to AWS, Azure, Kubernetes, and admin subsystems is **completely unreachable**. This is not a permissions issue — it is an infrastructure outage.\n\n---\n\n## Tool Execution Matrix\n\n| # | Tool | Cloud | Purpose | Result |\n|:-:|------|:-----:|---------|:------:|\n| 1 | `aws_cost_summary` | AWS | Total MTD spend | ❌ ECONNREFUSED |\n| 2 | `aws_cost_by_service` | AWS | Service breakdown | ❌ ECONNREFUSED |\n| 3 | `aws_identity` | AWS | Account identity | ❌ ECONNREFUSED |\n| 4 | `azure_cost_query` | Azure | MTD cost query | ❌ ECONNREFUSED |\n| 5 | `azure_cost_by_service` | Azure | Service breakdown | ❌ ECONNREFUSED |\n| 6 | `azure_cost_forecast` | Azure | EOM projection | ❌ ECONNREFUSED |\n| 7 | `azure_list_subscriptions` | Azure | Subscription inventory | ❌ ECONNREFUSED |\n| 8 | `call_aws` (CE API direct) | AWS | Fallback cost query | ❌ ECONNREFUSED |\n| 9 | `azure_arm_execute` (CostMgmt) | Azure | Fallback ARM query | ❌ ECONNREFUSED |\n| 10 | `admin_system_infrastructure_health_check` | Platform | Infra diagnostics | ❌ ECONNREFUSED |\n| 11 | `k8s_cluster_health` | Platform | Cluster state | ❌ ECONNREFUSED |\n| 12 | `admin_system_postgres_health_check` | Platform | Database state | ❌ ECONNREFUSED |\n\n---\n\n## Root Cause Analysis\n\n### Failure Point: MCP Proxy Pod (`10.43.224.106:8080`)\n\nEvery tool routes through the MCP proxy at this ClusterIP. The pod is either **crashed, OOM-killed, or evicted**.\n\n```diagram\n{\n  \"type\": \"flowchart\",\n  \"title\": \"MCP Proxy Failure — Blast Radius\",\n  \"layout\": \"vertical\",\n  \"nodes\": [\n    {\"id\": \"user\", \"label\": \"User Request\\n(Cost Analysis)\", \"shape\": \"rounded\", \"color\": \"primary\"},\n    {\"id\": \"proxy\", \"label\": \"MCP Proxy\\n10.43.224.106:8080\\n❌ ECONNREFUSED\", \"shape\": \"hexagon\", \"color\": \"error\"},\n    {\"id\": \"aws\", \"label\": \"AWS MCP\\n(Cost Explorer, STS)\", \"shape\": \"cloud\", \"color\": \"muted\"},\n    {\"id\": \"azure\", \"label\": \"Azure MCP\\n(ARM, Cost Mgmt)\", \"shape\": \"cloud\", \"color\": \"muted\"},\n    {\"id\": \"admin\", \"label\": \"Admin MCP\\n(Postgres, Redis, Milvus)\", \"shape\": \"cylinder\", \"color\": \"muted\"},\n    {\"id\": \"k8s\", \"label\": \"Kubernetes MCP\\n(Cluster Health)\", \"shape\": \"rectangle\", \"color\": \"muted\"}\n  ],\n  \"edges\": [\n    {\"source\": \"user\", \"target\": \"proxy\", \"label\": \"12 tool calls\", \"style\": \"solid\"},\n    {\"source\": \"proxy\", \"target\": \"aws\", \"label\": \"BLOCKED\", \"style\": \"dashed\"},\n    {\"source\": \"proxy\", \"target\": \"azure\", \"label\": \"BLOCKED\", \"style\": \"dashed\"},\n    {\"source\": \"proxy\", \"target\": \"admin\", \"label\": \"BLOCKED\", \"style\": \"dashed\"},\n    {\"source\": \"proxy\", \"target\": \"k8s\", \"label\": \"BLOCKED\", \"style\": \"dashed\"}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Correlation with Previous Audits\n\nThis is a **known, recurring failure** — now observed across **4 consecutive audits**:\n\n| Audit | MCP Proxy | AWS Tools | Azure Tools | Admin Tools | K8s Tools |\n|:-----:|:---------:|:---------:|:-----------:|:-----------:|:---------:|\n| Audit 1 | ⚠️ Partial | ✅ | ✅ | ❌ Crashed | ❌ No kubeconfig |\n| Audit 2 | ⚠️ Partial | ✅ | ✅ | ❌ Crashed | ❌ No kubeconfig |\n| Audit 3 | ⚠️ Partial | ✅ | ✅ | ❌ Crashed | ❌ No kubeconfig |\n| **This Audit** | **❌ Total outage** | **❌ Unreachable** | **❌ Unreachable** | **❌ Unreachable** | **❌ Unreachable** |\n\n> [!CAUTION]\n> **This is an escalation, not a repeat.** Previous audits had partial connectivity (AWS/Azure MCP worked while Admin/K8s failed). Now the **entire proxy is down**, blocking all cloud operations including cost visibility.\n\n---\n\n## Immediate Actions Required\n\n| Priority | Action | Why |\n|:--------:|--------|-----|\n| **P0** | **Restart MCP proxy pod** — `kubectl rollout restart deployment/openagentic-mcp-proxy -n openagentic` | Total platform blindness — no cloud operations possible. This is the **4th recurrence**. |\n| **P0** | **Check pod status** — `kubectl get pods -n openagentic -l app=openagentic-mcp-proxy` — look for OOMKilled, CrashLoopBackOff, or Evicted | Need RCA before restart to prevent immediate re-crash |\n| **P0** | **Collect crash logs** — `kubectl logs -n openagentic -l app=openagentic-mcp-proxy --previous` | Capture evidence before the restart overwrites logs |\n| **P1** | **Add PodDisruptionBudget + 2 replicas** for MCP proxy | 4 consecutive failures prove SPOF architecture is unacceptable. A single pod crash blinds the entire platform. |\n| **P1** | **Add liveness probe** on `:8080/health` with `failureThreshold: 3` | Kubernetes should auto-restart the proxy before it reaches total ECONNREFUSED state |\n| **P1** | **Increase memory limits** if OOMKilled — check `kubectl describe pod` for `LastState.Terminated.Reason` | Previous audits flagged Prisma connection pool exhaustion as a possible memory pressure source |\n\n---\n\n## What I Will Deliver Once Connectivity Is Restored\n\nOnce the MCP proxy is back online, I will immediately re-execute the full analysis:\n\n- [ ] **AWS**: Total MTD spend, service breakdown, account identity\n- [ ] **Azure**: MTD cost query, service breakdown, 30-day forecast, subscription inventory\n- [ ] **Combined**: Unified cost table, top 5 cost drivers, projected monthly total\n- [ ] **Optimization**: 3+ specific cost reduction recommendations\n- [ ] **Anomaly detection**: Flag services with unusual spend patterns\n\n---\n\n## Bottom Line\n\n> **The cost analysis cannot be completed because the MCP proxy — the single gateway to all cloud APIs — is in a total outage state.** This is the 4th audit where this component has failed, and the first where it has taken down *all* cloud connectivity (previously only Admin/K8s were affected). **Restoring this pod is a P0 prerequisite** to any cloud operations, including cost analysis. The persistent single-replica, no-probe architecture must be addressed to prevent recurrence.\n\n**Please restart the MCP proxy pod and notify me — I will re-run the full 7-call cost analysis immediately.**"}

